universum.studios.android.intent

Class MapIntent

  • java.lang.Object
    • universum.studios.android.intent.BaseIntent<MapIntent>
      • universum.studios.android.intent.MapIntent

  • public class MapIntent
extends BaseIntent<MapIntent>
    A BaseIntent builder implementation providing API for building and starting of intents targeting a maps related applications.

    Location via latitude + longitude

    Simple intent to show map at a specific location can be created by specifying just latitude and longitude via location(double, double). You can also specify either label for the requested location via label(String) or zoom level via zoomLevel(int).

    Location via query

    In case when you want to show map at a specific location, but you do not know its exact location (lat + lng), you can specify location query via locationQuery(String), which can contain name of place (town/city) and state that you want to show on map. In this case you can also specify the location label via label(String) as for lat + lng based map intent.
    Author:
    Martin Albedinsky
